# Analysis of the Main Target Image

## Count & Layers:
The structure consists of multiple building blocks arranged in several groups:
- A central tall structure with orange cylindrical pillars
- An orange triangular roof piece at the top
- Yellow rectangular blocks serving as platforms
- Red, blue, and green cubic blocks
- A separate small structure to the left

The main structure appears to have 3 vertical layers:
1. Base: Two orange cylindrical pillars
2. Middle: Yellow rectangular blocks with red and blue cubes
3. Top: A tall orange cylindrical piece with an orange triangular roof

## Spatial Relationships:
- Two orange cylindrical pillars (index 12) form the base of the main structure
- A long orange cylindrical piece (index 12) extends vertically from the left pillar
- Yellow rectangular blocks (indices 10 and 11) are placed horizontally across the pillars
- A red cube (index 1) sits on the left yellow rectangular block
- A blue cube (index 6) sits on the right yellow rectangular block
- An orange triangular piece (index 15) sits atop the tall orange cylinder

The separate structure on the left consists of:
- A blue cube (index 6) at the bottom left
- A red cube (index 1) in the middle
- A green cube (index 7) at the right
- A yellow rectangular block (index 11) placed horizontally on top
- An orange triangular piece (index 15) sits on the yellow rectangular block

# Required Blocks from Dictionary

Based on the analysis, I need the following blocks from the dictionary:
- Orange cylindrical blocks (index 12) - used 3 times
- Yellow rectangular blocks (index 10 and 11) - used 4 times
- Red cubic blocks (index 1) - used 2 times
- Blue cubic blocks (index 6) - used 2 times
- Green cubic block (index 7) - used 1 time
- Orange triangular pieces (index 15) - used 2 times

# Assembly Order

```
{
   Step1: Move block with index 12
   Step2: Move block with index 12
   Step3: Move block with index 12

   Step7: Move block with index 6

   Step9: Move block with index 6
   Step10: Move block with index 1

   Step12: Move block with index 11
   Step13: Move block with index 15
}
```
